{{Infobox_gene}}
'''Poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase family member 14''' is a [[protein]] that, in [[Human|humans]], is encoded by the PARP14 [[gene]].
<ref name="entrez">
{{cite web
| title = Entrez Gene: Poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase family member 14
| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/54625
| accessdate = 2016-03-02
}}</ref>

==Function==
Poly(ADP-ribosyl)ation is an immediate [[DNA]] damage-dependent [[post-translational modification]] of [[Histone|histones]] and other [[Nuclear protein|nuclear proteins]] that contributes to the survival of injured proliferating cells. PARP14 belongs to the superfamily of [[Enzyme|enzymes]] that perform this modification (Ame et al., 2004 [PubMed 15273990]).

