{{Infobox video game | title = pou game | collapsible = | state = | image = Pou game screenshot.jpg | caption = A customized Pou | developer = [[Paul Salameh]] <ref name="a">{{cite web |url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=me.pou.app |title=Pou - Android Apps on Google Play |website=Google Play |date=2014-03-16 |accessdate=2014-03-20}}</ref><ref name="b">{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/ph/app/pou/id575154654?mt=8 |title=Pou on the App Store on iTunes |website=iTunes |date=2014-03-13 |accessdate=2014-03-20}}</ref> | publisher = | series = 1 | engine = | platforms = [[Android (operating system)|Android]],<ref name="a"/> [[iOS]],<ref name="b"/> [[BlackBerry 10]] | released = 5 August 2012<ref name="a"/> | genre = | modes = }}
'''Pou''' is a [[digital pet|virtual pet]] game for [[BlackBerry 10]], [[iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]] developed and published by Paul Salameh (listed as Zakeh on the Google Play Store).<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/pr/1430883 |title=Report: Famous Mobile Apps Now Discussed in Chatwing 3.0 - Press Release |newspaper=Digital Journal |date=2013-08-24 |accessdate=2013-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.wamda.com/2013/05/the-24-year-old-lebanese-entrepreneur-behind-pou-top-mobile-kids-game |title=How a 24-year-old Lebanese entrepreneur found global success by beating Tamagotchi at their own game {{!}} Wamda.com |first=Nina |last=Curley |date=2013-05-16 |newspaper=Wamda.com |accessdate=2014-03-20}}</ref> It features a rounded, triangular alien character whose default color is brown. In the game the character can be fed, cleaned, exercised, suited, and put to sleep. There are also mini games within the app and coins can be earned to purchase costumes, decorations, and modifications of the game environment by playing the mini game or by reaching the achievements. It is somewhat similar to [[Tamagotchi]], a fad game that required caring for a simulated creature.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tecmundo.com.br/como-fazer/43363-como-instalar-e-jogar-o-pou-sucesso-do-android-no-computador.htm |title=Como instalar e jogar o Pou, sucesso do Android, no computador |trans-title=How to install and play the Pou, success of Android on your computer |newspaper=TecMundo |first=Caroline |last=Hecke |language=Portuguese|date=2013-08-16 |accessdate=2013-09-15}}</ref> It can also interact with other Pous by visiting them when the game is connected to the internet or play games with other Pous as opponent via selected mini games which as Pou-vs-Pou (PvP) capability the game connectivity is either [[Wi-Fi]], [[Bluetooth]], or even via [[Internet]]. It has user account in order to save and back-up the game progress state, in case the device is cleared. The last game progress can be resumed by logging in the user's account. The user can also transfer Pou from one device to another regardless of platform by logging out his/her account from the device and logging into other device; however the application version must be same between the two devices. In 2014, multilingual support was added.
With the success of the game, it has been copied using the name Mou on [[Windows Phone]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://poudownload.com/download-pou-for-windows-phone/ |title=New Pou for Windows Phone called Mou! |website=Pou Download |date=2013-10-30 |accessdate=2013-10-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.windowsphone.com/es-es/store/app/mou/c032d62c-7f6a-4538-8150-f77034dcf335 |title=Mou - Windows Phone |website=Windows Phone (Spain) |language=Spanish |date=2013-10-30 |accessdate=2013-10-30}}</ref>
